# <type>(scope): <subject> (50 characters)
# -----------------------------------------------
#
# Explain why this change is being made (72 characters)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------

# Types:
#    chore    (updating grunt tasks etc; no production code change)
#    build    (changes done to build system)
#    docs     (changes to documentation)
#    feat     (new feature)
#    fix      (bug fix)
#    perf     (code that improves performance)
#    refactor (refactoring production code)
#    style    (formatting, missing semi colons, etc; no code change)
#    test     (adding or feactoring tests; no production code change)
#
# * Capitalize the subject line (optional)
# * Use the imperative mood in the subject line
# * Do not end the subject line with a period
# * Separate the subject from body with a blank line
# * Use the body to explain what and why vs. how
# * Can use multiple lines with "-" or "*" for bullet points in body
#
# TIP: <type>! draws attention to breaking change
# TIP: 'BREAKING CHANGE' in body should describe breaking change
#
# https://www.conventionalcommits.org
